Address ranges to be use by private networks are:

    Class A: 10.0.0.0 to 10.255.255.255
    Class B: 172.16.0.0 to 172.31.255.255
    Class C: 192.168.0.0 to 192.168.255.255

some different subnets for class A are 10.0.x.x and 10.1.x.x

some different subnets for class B are 172.16.x.x and 172.23.x.x 

some different subnets for class C are 192.168.x.x and 192.68.50.x


If you have a system with multiple NIC be sure that the 2 NICS are connected to different subnes!

Follow also other tips inside this repo!



the thing really important if you want to stay in private networks, is that you must stay in these intervals

Any other IP is considered public
